We recommend that the Local Chief Executive instruct the following officials of the Municipality to undertake the following measures:

a)	Direct the Inventory Committee to conduct complete physical count of Property, Plant and Equipment on annual basis and for Inventories for every six (6) months;

b)	Direct the Inventory Committee to prepare the Inventory Report using the prescribed format, Report of the Physical Count of Inventories (RPCI) for Inventories and Report of Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) for Property, Plant and Equipment and submit the same to the Audit Team not later than January 31 of the following year;

c)	The inventory listing of the equipment should be compared with the property card maintained by the Municipal General Services Office as against the equipment ledger cards maintained by the Office of the Municipal Accountant and the total thereof should be reconciled;

d)	All discrepancies noted between physical and book inventories must be investigated, cleared and reconciled. If necessary, written explanation should be required from accountable and responsible person. In addition, the Office of the Municipal Accountant should continue its effort to locate pertinent source documents to reduce the unidentified balances in the property ledger cards, if any, in order to render a complete and accurate financial report.

